Fono NimbleX SlackBuild
=======================

Two build modes — pick one:

* Binary mode (default, fastest, no build dependencies):

    ./fono.SlackBuild                 # fetches the published musl binary

  The build script downloads
  `fono-v<VERSION>-<arch>-unknown-linux-musl.tar.gz` from the GitHub
  release pinned in `fono.info`. Override the release base URL with
  `FONO_RELEASE_BASE=https://mirror.example/fono ./fono.SlackBuild`.

* Source mode (requires rust + rustup with a musl target installed):

    FROM_SOURCE=1 ./fono.SlackBuild

Standard SlackBuild environment variables also apply:
`ARCH`, `VERSION`, `BUILD`, `TAG`, `PKGTYPE`, `TMP`, `OUTPUT`.

The resulting package installs:

* `/usr/bin/fono`                         — the single static binary
* `/usr/share/applications/fono.desktop`  — desktop entry
* `/usr/share/icons/hicolor/scalable/apps/fono.svg`
* `/lib/systemd/user/fono.service`        — per-user unit (never enabled
                                             system-wide; users opt in
                                             with `systemctl --user
                                             enable --now fono.service`)
* Shell completions for bash / zsh / fish under the usual locations
  (generated post-install via `fono completions`).

Config, models, and history live under the invoking user's XDG dirs;
`removepkg fono` does **not** touch them — that data is user state.

Optional runtime dependencies
-----------------------------

Fono works out of the box on Slackware — `libxkbcommon-x11` is bundled
inside the core `libxkbcommon` package, so the on-screen overlay's
X11 / Xwayland backend works without extra installs. For auto-typing
into other applications, install ONE of the following from SBo (none
are required; without them Fono still delivers dictation via the
clipboard):

* `xdotool`   — auto-typing on X11 and XWayland (works on GNOME-Wayland
                and any other Wayland session via XWayland)
* `wtype`     — auto-typing on native Wayland (wlroots family: sway,
                hyprland, river, wayfire; and KDE Plasma's KWin)
* `ydotool`   — universal Wayland injector, needs you to run
                `ydotoold` with `/dev/uinput` access; not auto-driven
                by `fono install`

`fono` detects which one is available at startup and uses it; the
package is not declared in `REQUIRES=` so SBo's build chain is not
forced on users who don't need it.
